==English==
===Etymology===
Compare French ''[[:fr:granulaire|granulaire]]''. See [[granule]]

===Adjective===
'''granular'''

#Consisting of, or resembling, grains; as, a granular substance. Grainy.  Granular limestone, crystalline limestone, or marble, having a granular structure. 

===Usage Notes===
The term "more granular" is ambiguous and should be avoided: it is not clear whether it indicates finer or coarser granularity.  It could mean that the grains are more plentiful (finer granularity), or it could mean that the grains are more pronounced (coarser granularity).  If a photograph is "more grainy", it means that the grain particles are larger (coarser) and thus more distinctly visible.  However, even though "grainy" is a synonym of "granular", the term "more granular" sometimes means the opposite of "more grainy".

===Quotations===
*'''1790,''' Abraham Mills, ''Some Strata in Ireland and Scotland,'' in ''Philosophical Transactions of the Royal Society of London,'' Vol. 80
*:This Whyn Dyke is bare at the cliffs ſeveral yards in height, and is near nine feet in width. It conſiſts of an inner part of a '''granular''' and ſomewhat porous texture...
